squat
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:verb
Sense Number:
Definition:(chiefly early North Island, from orig US sense) to settle on an area of public land before acquiring a legal right to it.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
